# Rimon Judaica - Project Guidelines & Cursor Rules

## 1. Project Context & Identity
- **Project Name:** Rimon Judaica (Premium Boutique e-commerce).
- **Tech Stack:** Monorepo (Turborepo/Nx), React (Vite), Node.js, Supabase (PostgreSQL), Zod, Framer Motion.
- **Tone:** Professional, luxury, minimalist, and clean.

## 2. Architecture & Code Structure
- **Monorepo Awareness:** - Shared types go to `packages/shared-types`.
    - Backend logic goes to `apps/core-service`.
    - Frontend components go to `apps/storefront`.
- **Imports:** Always check `@rimon/shared-types` before creating new local interfaces. Use absolute imports where configured.
- **Component Pattern:** Logic (Hooks/Context) must be separated from UI. Use CSS Modules for styling.

## 3. UI & UX (RTL & Luxury Design)
- **RTL First:** All components must support Right-to-Left (Hebrew) natively. 
    - Use Logical Properties: `padding-inline-start` instead of `padding-right`, `inset-inline-start` instead of `right`.
- **Design System:** Use ONLY defined CSS variables (e.g., `--color-primary`, `--color-accent`). 
    - Primary Accent: Deep Burgundy.
    - Base: White/Cream.
- **Minimalism:** Sharp corners (low border-radius), plenty of whitespace, elegant Serif headings, and clean Sans-Serif body text.
- **Visual References:** Follow the minimalist aesthetic of high-end boutique studios. Do NOT mention specific external studio names in code or comments.

## 4. Documentation & Language
- **Coding Language:** All code (variables, functions, filenames) must be in English.
- **User Interface:** All customer-facing text (Labels, Buttons, Toasts, Placeholders) must be in high-quality Hebrew.
- **Docstrings:** Every exported function, hook, or component must have a JSDoc block in **English** explaining:
    - What it does.
    - Parameters and return values.
    - Any business logic implications (e.g., "Restores stock upon deletion").

## 5. Security & Data Integrity
- **Supabase & RLS:** Every new table must include Row Level Security (RLS) policies. Default is `RESTRICT`.
- **Secrets:** Never hardcode API keys or secrets. Use `.env` variables and verify their existence before use.
- **Validation:** Use `Zod` for all API request/response validation and form handling.
- **Stock Integrity:** Logic involving `stock_quantity` must be atomic. Ensure stock is restored to `product_variants` when an item is removed from a cart.

## 6. Interactions & Motion
- **Transitions:** Use `framer-motion` for smooth, subtle UI transitions (hover effects, scroll-based animations).
- **Scroll Effects:** Header transitions must be smooth (using `max-width` and `margin: auto` to prevent layout shifts).

## 7. Performance
- **Images:** Use lazy loading for all product images. 
- **Icons:** Use thin outline-style icons only.